Misty =96 this gives me hope.  I am so new to this and not technical in the=

least.  I wish I had 24 hours a day to dedicate to ITC but I have small
ch=
ildren and they seem to take all my time.  I am hoping to find a few hours
=
to modify that RS and really begin my attempts.  I am very grateful that
th=
is low tech idea was passed onto to us!  Just 3 weeks ago I too lost my
nie=
ce (17yrs) and nephew (14yrs) to a car accident.  Aly, my niece died on
imp=
act, but her brother Ryan hung on for 4 more days and I was there with my
s=
ister (his mom) and his dad when they ended life support.  I don=92t know i=
f
it is too soon.. but what a wonderful gift I could give my sister if I co=
uld
capture their voices and let her know that her two children are still w=
ith
us.

k



  _____  

From: EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com [mailto:EVP-ITC@yah=
oogroups.com] On Behalf Of
Misty Dawn
Sent: Wednesday, November 28, 2007 1:=
36 AM
To: EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com
Subject: Re: [EVP-ITC] Re: New file uploa=
ded to EVP-ITC



Glad she made it thru but sorry it had to be this way. I=
 understand how that
feels. Yes on the training part too, I have gotten tha=
t quite often over the
years when new spirits begin to speak sometimes the =
others help them or even
speak for them if they arent getting across clearl=
y. Sometimes its very
detailed instructions that blow my mind. But it is in=
teresting to listen to
thier conversations there. 



I also used to notic=
e that sometimes when I would try a new method it would
be almost as if my =
close contacts would go to another broadcasting station,
go in, introduce t=
hemselves and announce they were there to speak to me or
the relation to me=
 then take over the session. Sometimes I think different
methods invite new=
 contacts/entities. However many of the contacts remain
the same and will u=
se any method I choose. 



Losing so many people on this side only streng=
thens the bonds to that side
more. Of that I have no doubt. It&#39;s the ties t=
hat bind. Very true statement.
For those who havent experienced loss its a =
bit of a different experience
overall. Theres nothing that can compare to h=
earing a voice thats been dead
for so long or that you thought you would ne=
ver hear again in this lifetime.
Some of you know how that feels. It just h=
its such a high note that it
resonates thru your spirit sometimes. In my ca=
se I have too many best
friends, loved ones, relations who went before me a=
nd did keep thier promise
to stay in touch whatever it took. 



Only when=
 we were all making those promises so many years ago we were just
saying it=
 more for the joke of it rather than the reality of it. One by one
they all=
 crossed over, and one by one they have kept thier promises. 



So, that =
being said

&quot;If I die before you die I&#39;m coming back to haunt you all&quot;



=
  &lt;http://us.i1.yimg.com/us.yimg.com/i/mesg/tsmileys2/03.gif&gt; 

Misty




=
Steve Hultay &lt;urkel23@...&gt; wrote:

Yeah, since i start using the Radio =
Shack radios i have been getting 
full sentence conversations with them. I&#39;=
ve been trying to contact 
my ex-girlfriend that passed last year at 29. Th=
at does sound like 
her voice, she has been coming through since Sunday nig=
ht and i 
actually heard them through the radio telling her to talk and she=

said &quot;Hi Steve&quot;. They were like training her to use the radio, 
pretty we=
ird stuff but it was good to hear from her in her own 
voice. The response =
time is remarkable with these radios, they seem 
to answer right away very =
&quot;frank&#39;s box&quot;-like. These will keep me 
occupied while i wait for #27---the=
 #13 replacement. I&#39;m really 
excited about that one, it may be the one to =
live up to for all 
future boxes. I&#39;m sure Frank could buy a radio shack bo=
x and add a 
sound chamber, that would probably really enhance the voices. =
These 
other boxes and radios are great, but there&#39;s only one Frank&#39;s Box 
=
for all others to try to live up to. I don&#39;t think a 10 Minute mod 
on a $2=
5 dollar radio will ever replace the time and effort frank 
puts into his b=
oxes. But anybody can try these radios and that&#39;s 
what is important, but w=
ithout Frank there would have been no 
advancement in ITC. Someone had to b=
reak the ground work.

-Steve H.

